did.unittitle: Alumni Records Office, Yale University, records of alumni from the Classes of 1701-1978

repository.corpname: Yale University. Department of Manuscripts and Archives

did.abstract: The records consist of biographical information about Yale graduates and non-graduates from the Classes of 1701-1978. Files on individual alumni may contain addresses, freshman registration forms, obituaries, newspaper clippings, and correspondence. Also included are informational cards documenting occupations, places of employment, other degrees, accomplishments, spouses, and children.

odd.head: General note
odd.p: Forms part of Yale Record Group 8-B (YRG 8-B), Records on individual Yale alumni.

accessrestrict.head: Conditions Governing Access
accessrestrict.p: Alumni records are restricted for 75 years from the last known date of attendance.

prefercite.head: Preferred Citation
prefercite.p: Alumni Records Office, Yale University, Records of Alumni from the Classes of 1701-1978 (RU 830). Manuscripts and Archives, Yale University Library.

processinfo.head: Processing Information
processinfo.p: Yale University records are arranged and described at the accession level by the creating office. The University Archives creates collection level descriptive records, but typically does no further arrangement and description at the accession level.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The series have varied filing schemes for graduate and non-graduate files, and the type of degree received.

Graduates and Non-Graduates . In general, non-graduate files are identified with an "x" either before or after the year of graduation. In some sections, graduate and non-graduate files in the same class are filed together in alphabetical order. In other sections, the non-graduate files follow the graduate files of the same class. In still other sections, the non-graduate files are kept completely separate from the chronological sequence of the graduate files. If a file is not found in the graduate section, make sure to also check among the non-graduate files.

Type of Degree . In some sections, graduate files with different types of degrees are interfiled according to their class. In other sections, graduate files with different types of degrees are filed separately with their own chronological sequence.

The following explanations for each series will show the varied treatment of files for graduates and non-graduates, and different types of degrees. The explanations should be used in conjunction with the box list.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The records are arranged in eleven series: I. Yale College. II. Sheffield Scientific School. III. School of Medicine. IV. Law School. V. Divinity School. VI. Graduate School of Arts & Science. VII. School of Nursing. VIII. Honorary Degrees. IX. School of Music. X. Art and Architecture XI. School of Forestry and Environmental Studies; and in subsequent accessions.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Each class (1701 to 1949) is divided into two sections for graduate and non-graduate files. Files for non-graduates follow the graduates of the same class. For example, the file for "Joe Smith, x1902" would be found in Box 159 in the 1902 non-graduate section directly after the files for the 1902 graduates. [Boxes 1-619].
For the Classes 1950 to 1954, files for non-graduates and graduates are filed together according to their class. [Boxes 620-633]

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Classes 1849 to 1945 contain files for Sheffield and Engineering graduates and non-graduates. Even though Sheffield became part of Yale College in 1935, the alumni records for Sheffield were still kept separately. Each class is divided into two sections for graduates and non-graduates. Non-graduates follow the graduates of the same class. For example, the file for "Joe Smith, x1902 s" would be found in box 694 in the 1902 non-graduate section directly after the files for the 1902 graduates. [Boxes 634-904]
For the Class of 1945 (with degrees We and Ws), files for non-graduates follow the graduates of the same class. [Boxes 904-907]
For the Class of 1946, files for non-graduates follow the graduates of the same class. [Boxes 907-909]
The files for the Class of 1946 with the Mar E&S degree are in Box 909.
For the Classes of 1947-1950, Undergraduate Engineering, files for non-graduates follow the graduates of the same class. [Boxes 910-914]
Files for students graduating from 1936 to 1949 with the Doctorate of Engineering (D.Eng.) are filed as a separate group. [Box 915]
Files for students graduating from 1936 to 1949 with the Master of Engineering (M.Eng.) are filed as a separate group. [Boxes 915-916]
Files for students graduating from 1936 to 1949 with miscellaneous engineering degrees (Misc. Degree) are filed as a separate group. [Boxes 916-917]

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents

Files for students graduating from 1920-1949 with a Doctorate of Public Health (D.P.H.) are filed separately. Non-graduate files are kept in a different section. [Box 942]
Files for non-graduate public health students, regardless of degree (Non-graduate M.P.H. and D.P.H.), are filed together for the years 1920 to 1949. [Box 943]

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: Files for students graduating from 1942 to 1951 with the Bachelor or Master of Architecture (B. Arch. or M. Arch.) are filed as a group. Files for non-graduates for these years are filed with the non-graduate art students. [Box 1164]

Files for students graduating from 1887 to 1949 with the Bachelor of Fine Arts (Art, Drama, and Architecture B.F.A.) are filed as a group. Students with concentrations in Painting, Sculpture, and Drama are included up to 1949, but students with a concentration in Architecture are only included up to 1941. Non-graduate files are in a different section. [Boxes 1164-1171]
Files for students graduating from 1928 to 1949 with miscellaneous degrees (Misc. Degree) in art are filed as a group. [Box 1171]

Files for students graduating from 1928 to 1949 with the Master of Fine Arts (Art, Drama, and Architecture M.F.A.) are filed as a group. Students with concentrations in Painting, Sculpture, Graphic Design, and Drama are included up to 1949, but students with a concentration in Architecture are only included up to 1941. Students with a doctorate may also be found here. Non-graduate files are in a different section. [Boxes 1172-1173]
Files for students graduating from 1879 to 1948 with the Certificate of Art (cart or artc) are filed as a separate group. Non-graduate files are in a different section. [Boxes 1174-1176]
Files for all non-graduate art, architecture, and drama students (1873x-1949x), regardless of degree (All Degrees), are filed as a group, separate from their class. [Boxes 1176-1190]
Files for students (1873-1949) with a special art degree or status are filed as a separate group. [Box 1191]
Files for all art and architecture students (1950-1954), graduates and non-graduates, regardless of degree (All Degrees), are filed together according to year. [Box 1192]
Files for all drama students (1950-1954), graduates and non-graduates, regardless of degree (All Degrees), are filed together according to year. [Box 1193]
For an explanation of the codes used for Fine Art degrees, see Appendix.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: For the Classes 1902 to 1949, each year is divided into two sections for graduate and non-graduate files. Files for non-graduates follow the graduates of the same class. [Boxes 1194-1213]
Files for graduates and non-graduates (1950-1954) are filed together according to year. [Box 1213]

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The materials consist of alumni death notices, obituaries and general biographical information for Yale undergraduate and graduate members of the Classess 1909-1958 who died during the period 1980-2005.
The materials are arranged chronologically by Class, thereunder alphabetically by last name.
